                    	<note xml:id="n_remarks" type="remarks">
                    	    
                                    
<p>Lettercard (one 2½-cent, two 5-cent stamps). Postmarks: ‘NUENEN 8-12 V 17 JANV 84’, ‘ARRAS A P<hi rend="italics">[x]</hi> / 18 JANV 84’ and ‘PARIS 3 (09) 3 / 8E. 18 JANV 84’. The address reads: ‘Monsieur Th van Gogh/ Maison Goupil &amp; Cie/ B Montmartre/ <hi rend="italics">Paris</hi>’.</p>
<p rend="indent">Vincent wrote two letters to Paris, one shortly after the other, on the same day: one to Theo’s work address and one to his home (<ref target="let423.xml">letters 423</ref> and <ref target="let424.xml">424</ref> respectively). We have reversed the order in respect of <hi rend="italics">De brieven</hi> 1990, because in the present letter we read: ‘I’m writing to your rue de Laval address by the same post’, which would seem to indicate that he had not yet done so. In <hi rend="italics">De brieven</hi> 1990 this letter was marked as not having been published before; this is incorrect; it has been known since the 1914 edition, under number 352.</p>
                                    
                                
                    	</note>
                    
                </listAnnotation>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="ogtnotes">
                    
                </listAnnotation>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            

<p>This was the Eindhoven doctor <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_495">A.L.K.H. van de Loo</rs> (FR b2266).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="a" xml:id="note-t-a">
                            

<p>The head of the femur is the name for that part of the thighbone that rotates in the hip socket.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p><rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_524">Mrs van Gogh</rs> had turned 64 in September.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
